title: Rockets claim No. 2 spot on power poll
text:
Rockets claim No. 2 spot on power poll Tim Johnson , Daily Herald Media 8:27 p.m. CDT October 5, 2015 Buy Photo Spencer/Columbus Catholic quarterback Calvin Lenz and the Rockets are leading the Cloverbelt Conference. (Photo: Gannett Central Wisconsin Media file photo) Buy Photo CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
WAUSAU â€” Undefeated Amherst maintains its firm hold on top spot in the local football power poll as the Falcons have since the start of the season. 
Spencer/Columbus Catholic moved up to No. 2, a spot that Edgar held before its loss to Marathon last week. The Rockets and Wildcats meet Friday in one of the top matchups for Week 8. Power Ranking 
The complete power poll follows. The poll is voted on by the Gannett Central Wisconsin Media sports staff. 
1. AMHERST (7-0): The Falcons have recovered 10 fumbles in seven games and returned two for touchdowns. Amherst hosts Weywauwega-Fremont Friday. 
2. SPENCER/COLUMBUS CATH (7-0): The Rockets have clinched a share of the Cloverbelt Conference championship. This week it's a nonconference matchup with Edgar. 
3. ABBOTSFORD (7-0): The Falcons were a preseason pick to finsh third in the Cloverwood. They are two wins away from an outright conference championship. 
4. ALMOND-BANCROFT (7-0): The Eagles have shut out five opponents and allowed 21 points this fall. Almond-Bancroft hosts Port Edwards Friday. 
5. EDGAR (6-1): The loss to Marathon snapped a 17-game winning streak for the Wildcats in the regular season and was their first loss at home since the 2013 postseason. Buy Photo Marathon beat Edgar, 16-8, at Edgar, Friday, October 2, 2015. Dan Young/Gannett Central Wisconsin Media Buy Photo
